body_html:
In my local run, the inputs to strided_slice were begin=[1], end=[0], strides=[1]. The strided_slice op is called as a part of the stft op.

With these inputs, strided_slice should either error out or return an empty tensor (since end < begin, which is causing the check to fail). We should likely do the latter since tensorflow itself doesn't error out.

I'm looping in rryan@ to see if these inputs to strided_slice make sense for stft and whether returning an empty tensor makes sense.

I've attached my model and frozen graph for debugging.
